Reading an image: cv2.imread()
image = cv2.imread("/content/image8.jpeg")
print(image.shape)
output : (100, 100, 3)

Displaying an image: cv2.imshow()
import cv2_imshow
cv2_imshow(image)


Writing an image: cv2.imwrite()

Resizing: cv2.resize()

Cropping: array slicing (img[100:300, 200:400])

Drawing: cv2.line(), cv2.rectangle(), cv2.circle(), cv2.putText()
